#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:32
msgid "Welcome to OTPClient"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:33
msgid ""
"A secure authenticator for TOTP and HOTP tokens.\n"
"\n"
"Your tokens are stored in encrypted databases protected by a master password."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:39
#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:100
msgid "Multiple Databases"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:40
msgid ""
"You can create and manage multiple encrypted databases.\n"
"\n"
"Use the sidebar to switch between them. Right-click a database to rename it, "
"set it as primary, or remove it from the list.\n"
"\n"
"The primary database is loaded automatically on startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:47
msgid "Organize with Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:48
msgid ""
"Organize your tokens into groups for quick filtering.\n"
"\n"
"Use the dropdown in the header bar to filter by group, or search with the "
"“group:” prefix. Assign groups by right-clicking a token."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:55
msgid "Keyboard Shortcuts & Search"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:56
msgid ""
"Use Ctrl+N to add a token, Ctrl+F to search, F2 to edit, and Ctrl+? to see "
"all shortcuts.\n"
"\n"
"Desktop search integration lets you find tokens from GNOME or KDE without "
"opening the app."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:64
msgid ""
"Secret Service integration can store your database password in the system "
"keyring so the app unlocks automatically after login. It is disabled by "
"default.\n"
"\n"
"You can enable it and configure auto-lock in Settings → Security."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:71
msgid "Settings & Backup"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:72
msgid ""
"All preferences are in the Settings dialog, including countdown colors and "
"clipboard auto-clear.\n"
"\n"
"Export and import your settings from Settings → Backup, or via the CLI with "
"--export-settings and --import-settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:84
msgid "A Brand New Look"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:85
msgid ""
"OTPClient has been completely redesigned with GTK4 and libadwaita.\n"
"\n"
"The interface is faster, follows modern GNOME conventions, and supports both "
"light and dark themes natively."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:92
msgid "Token Groups"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:93
msgid ""
"Organize your tokens into groups for quick access.\n"
"\n"
"Use the dropdown in the header bar to filter by group. Right-click a token "
"to assign it, or search with the “group:” prefix."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:101
msgid ""
"You can now manage multiple encrypted databases from the sidebar.\n"
"\n"
"Right-click a database to rename it, set it as primary, or remove it from "
"the list. The primary database loads on startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:107 ../src/gui/ui/window.ui:280
#: ../src/gui/ui/shortcuts-window.ui:4 ../src/gui/ui/shortcuts-window.ui:121
msgid "Keyboard Shortcuts"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/gui/dialogs/whats-new-dialog.c:108
msgid ""
"Common actions now have keyboard shortcuts: Ctrl+N to add, Ctrl+F to search, "
